> A way to store previous state of an object easily.

> Memento: The basic object that is stored in different states.

> Originator: Sets and gets values form the currently targeted Memento. Creates a new memento and assigns current values to them.

> Caretaker: Holds an ArrayList that contains all previous versions of the memento. It can store and retrieve memento.

> Memento pattern is used to restore state of an object to a previous state. 

> Memento pattern falls under behavioral pattern category.
